WEBVTT

00:02.004 --> 00:04.007
♪ OH, THE WEATHER OUTSIDE
IS FRIGHTFUL ♪

00:04.007 --> 00:07.647
♪ BUT THE FIRE
IS SO DELIGHTFUL ♪

00:07.647 --> 00:10.653
♪ AND SINCE
WE'VE NO PLACE TO GO ♪

00:10.653 --> 00:14.326
♪ LET IT SNOW,
LET IT SNOW, LET IT SNOW ♪

00:14.326 --> 00:18.033
♪ MAN, IT DOESN'T SHOW
SIGNS OF STOPPING ♪

00:18.033 --> 00:21.506
♪ AND I BROUGHT ME
SOME CORN FOR POPPING ♪

00:21.506 --> 00:25.179
♪ THE LIGHTS
ARE TURNED WAY DOWN LOW ♪

00:25.179 --> 00:28.653
♪ LET IT SNOW, LET IT SNOW ♪

00:28.653 --> 00:32.159
♪ WHEN WE FINALLY
KISS GOODNIGHT ♪

00:32.159 --> 00:35.632
♪ HOW I'LL HATE
GOING OUT IN THE STORM ♪

00:35.632 --> 00:39.639
♪ BUT IF YOU REALLY
HOLD ME TIGHT ♪

00:39.639 --> 00:43.012
♪ ALL THE WAY HOME
I'LL BE WARM ♪

00:43.012 --> 00:46.318
♪ OH, THE FIRE
IS SLOWLY DYING ♪

00:46.318 --> 00:50.159
♪ AND MY DEAR,
WE'RE STILL GOODBYE-ING ♪
[ GROANING, GASPING ]

00:50.159 --> 00:53.297
♪ BUT AS LONG
AS YOU LOVE ME SO ♪
OH! OH, MY GOD!

00:53.297 --> 00:56.203
♪ LET IT SNOW,
LET IT SNOW, LET IT SNOW ♪
OH, GET UP!
IT'S CHRISTMAS DAY!

00:56.203 --> 00:59.643
WHAT IS HAPPENING?
WHY AM I WEARING A SANTA SUIT?!

00:59.643 --> 01:02.081
I DON'T KNOW. I DON'T KNOW.
BUT THE KIDS ARE GONNA
BE UP ANY MINUTE NOW.

01:02.081 --> 01:03.516
WHY IS THERE
A DOG IN HERE?!

01:03.516 --> 01:05.353
I DON'T KNOW.
IT'S YOUR HOUSE.

01:05.353 --> 01:06.622
WHY IS THERE
A DOG IN HERE?

01:06.622 --> 01:07.757
WHAT ARE
YOU DOING HERE?

01:07.757 --> 01:10.161
I DON'T KNOW.
WHAT AM I DOING HERE?

01:10.161 --> 01:12.699
WHOA!
HANGOVER CITY.

01:12.699 --> 01:14.203
[ GASPS ]
OH, WOW!

01:14.203 --> 01:15.538
OH, GEEZ.

01:15.538 --> 01:17.141
OKAY,
JUST DON'T FREAK OUT.
WHAT?

01:17.141 --> 01:18.810
Y-YOU'RE FINE.

01:18.810 --> 01:21.081
JACKIE, SOMETHING TERRIBLE
HAS HAPPENED TO YOUR FACE.

01:21.081 --> 01:24.388
NO.
WHAT?! NUH-UNH!

01:24.388 --> 01:27.192
OH! THEY'RE GONNA
GROW BACK, RIGHT?

01:27.192 --> 01:29.063
YEAH.
BERT: I CAN'T WAIT
TO SEE WHAT HAPPENED!

01:29.063 --> 01:31.234
[ KIDS SHOUTING ]
IT'S THE KIDS. UH...

01:31.234 --> 01:34.239
[ GASPS ]
HEY.

01:34.239 --> 01:35.641
KATE: HEY, GUYS.

01:35.641 --> 01:38.280
HOLY CRAP.
CRAP.
CRAP.

01:38.280 --> 01:40.216
WHAT HAPPENED?

01:40.216 --> 01:41.619
MERRY CHRISTMAS.

01:41.619 --> 01:42.721
MERRY CHRISTMAS!

01:42.721 --> 01:47.129
DIANE: MERRY CHRISTMAS.
WHOO!

01:47.129 --> 01:50.135
♪♪♪

01:57.281 --> 01:59.218
WHAT HAPPENED
TO OUR HOUSE?

02:00.287 --> 02:03.693
OH, MY STARS!
THE TREE!

02:03.693 --> 02:04.695
[ GASPS ] LOOK AWAY, BERT!
LOOK AWAY!

02:04.695 --> 02:07.133
[ BARKS, SNARLS ]
[ ALL SCREAM ]

02:07.133 --> 02:09.136
WHAT IS THAT?!

02:09.136 --> 02:10.606
HE'S FRIENDLY. HE JUST
WANTS TO GET TO KNOW YOU.

02:10.606 --> 02:12.175
COME ON,
MY LITTLE ANGEL.

02:12.175 --> 02:14.279
YEAH, LET'S GO! LET'S GO LOOK
AT OUR BURNING TREE, GUYS!

02:14.279 --> 02:16.516
COME ON! GO! GO!
GREAT JOB, YOU GUYS.

02:16.516 --> 02:18.353
WHAT HAPPENED LAST NIGHT?
I MEAN...

02:18.353 --> 02:19.856
I DON'T REMEMBER.

02:19.856 --> 02:21.693
[ GROANS ]
NEITHER DO I.
NOT A THING.

02:21.693 --> 02:23.129
THE ONLY OTHER TIME

02:23.129 --> 02:25.133
I'VE EVER BLACKED OUT
LIKE THAT WAS FROM OPIUM.

02:25.133 --> 02:28.104
IT WAS IN MOROCCO.
IT WAS CUSTOMARY.

02:28.104 --> 02:29.373
[ CHUCKLES ]
I WAS BEING POLITE.

02:29.373 --> 02:32.546
LET'S GO BACK
TO WHAT WE DO REMEMBER.

02:32.546 --> 02:34.215
OH, GOD.
OOH, YES.
GOOD IDEA. SMART.

02:34.215 --> 02:35.852
UM, I REMEMBER
I HAD EYEBROWS.

02:35.852 --> 02:38.390
YEAH, AND I REMEMBER
I WAS MAKING DRINKS.

02:38.390 --> 02:39.793
WELL, ISN'T THAT
WHAT YOU DO EVERY DAY?

02:39.793 --> 02:41.629
[ SCOFFS ]

02:41.629 --> 02:44.233
♪♪♪

02:48.275 --> 02:50.278
MMM.

02:50.278 --> 02:51.413
YOU WANT TO
SEE A TRICK?

02:51.413 --> 02:53.250
SURE.

02:53.250 --> 02:54.753
THAT'S SO COOL!

02:54.753 --> 02:56.456
HOW DO YOU KNOW
HOW TO DO THAT?

02:56.456 --> 02:58.226
I WENT TO SCHOOL
FOR IT --

02:58.226 --> 03:00.163
THE VAN NUYS
INSTITUTE OF MIXOLOGY.

03:00.163 --> 03:01.666
THAT'S WHERE
I WANT TO GO!

03:01.666 --> 03:04.437
OH, BEST TWO WEEKS
OF MY LIFE.

03:04.437 --> 03:06.441
I JUST WANT TO
SAY FOR THE RECORD --

03:06.441 --> 03:07.643
BAH, HUMBUG.

03:07.643 --> 03:09.446
I KNEW WE SHOULDN'T
HAVE SENT YOU TO THE MALL.

03:09.446 --> 03:10.615
I SAW A WOMAN
TRIP ANOTHER WOMAN

03:10.615 --> 03:12.619
TO GET TO AN ELMO
WEARING A CHEF'S HAT.

03:12.619 --> 03:13.788
[ THUD, HUMMING ]

03:13.788 --> 03:15.157
OH, GREAT.

03:15.157 --> 03:17.161
HELENE'S POWERED UP
HER DECORATIONS.

03:17.161 --> 03:20.333
YOU KNOW, SHE ADDED
ANOTHER NATIVITY SCENE.

03:20.333 --> 03:22.604
THAT'S THREE. THAT'S NINE
WISE MEN, IF YOU COUNT.

03:22.604 --> 03:24.608
TAKE IT EASY. SHE LIKES
TO DECORATE FOR CHRISTMAS.

03:24.608 --> 03:26.645
YOU CAN SEE
THAT HOUSE FROM SPACE.

03:26.645 --> 03:28.181
WHAT'S THAT SMELL?

03:28.181 --> 03:30.252
OH, I'M MAKING GLOGG.
GLUG?

03:30.252 --> 03:32.221
GLOGG.
GLAG?

03:32.221 --> 03:34.492
GLOGG.
WHAT ARE WE DOING?

03:34.492 --> 03:35.661
IT'S MULLED WINE.
I JUST THOUGHT, YOU KNOW,

03:35.661 --> 03:36.830
IT'S MY FIRST CHRISTMAS
WITH YOU,

03:36.830 --> 03:37.899
AND I WANTED TO
INCORPORATE

03:37.899 --> 03:39.468
SOME OF MY SWEDISH
FAMILY TRADITIONS.

03:39.468 --> 03:41.438
ISN'T THIS A LOT
FOR JUST THE TWO OF US?

03:41.438 --> 03:44.377
YEAH, UM...I ACTUALLY
INVITED SOME PEOPLE,

03:44.377 --> 03:45.713
UH, PEOPLE YOU'VE MET,

03:45.713 --> 03:47.950
PEOPLE YOU MAY OR MAY NOT
HAVE BEEN MARRIED TO.

03:47.950 --> 03:49.620
KATE,
WE TALKED ABOUT THIS.

03:49.620 --> 03:52.358
WE HAVE A VERY STRICT
HOLIDAY ROTATION.

03:52.358 --> 03:54.562
THIS IS OUR YEAR.
WE HAVE THE THREE KIDS.

03:54.562 --> 03:56.934
[ CHUCKLES ]
NO DIANE AND NO JACKIE.

03:56.934 --> 03:58.636
I KNOW, PETE.
AND YOU KNOW WHAT?

03:58.636 --> 04:01.876
364 DAYS OUT OF THE YEAR,
I'M TOTALLY ON YOUR SIDE.

04:01.876 --> 04:05.182
BUT IT'S CHRISTMAS, BABE.
FAMILY SHOULD BE TOGETHER.

04:05.182 --> 04:06.251
OKAY, FINE.

04:06.251 --> 04:08.722
WE'LL GIVE THEM A COOKIE,
GLASS OF WINE,

04:08.722 --> 04:10.892
FA LA LA,
OUT THE DOOR THEY GO.

04:10.892 --> 04:12.195
[ SIGHS ]

04:12.195 --> 04:13.664
DON'T WORRY, SCROOGE.
IT'LL BE GREAT.

04:13.664 --> 04:15.768
HERE. DRINK UP.

04:15.768 --> 04:17.571
SEE? SHE WAS
PUSHING THAT ON EVERYBODY.

04:17.571 --> 04:20.276
W-W-WHAT WAS YOUR ANGLE,
KATE?

04:20.276 --> 04:21.746
TO GET US ALL SO DRUNK

04:21.746 --> 04:24.284
SO YOU COULD STAY UP
AND TRY ON MY LOUBOUTINS?

04:24.284 --> 04:24.985
MM-HMM.
I'VE SEEN THE WAY
YOU LOOK AT THEM.

04:24.985 --> 04:27.322
OOH, OOH!

04:27.322 --> 04:28.825
IT WAS PROBABLY
TO TRY ON MY MOCCASINS.

04:28.825 --> 04:30.762
YEAH, I'VE SEE THE WAY
YOU LOOK AT THEM.

04:30.762 --> 04:33.968
I JUST WANTED US
TO HAVE A NICE CHRISTMAS.

04:33.968 --> 04:36.206
WELL, I FOR ONE,
HATED THE GLOGG.

04:36.206 --> 04:38.476
[ CHUCKLES ]
I LOVE THIS GLOGG!

04:38.476 --> 04:40.646
YOU HAVE TO GIVE ME
THE RECIPE, PRONTO.

04:40.646 --> 04:43.486
OH, THAT'S ITALIAN
FOR "ARRIBA, ARRIBA!"

04:43.486 --> 04:44.821
[ SNAPS FINGERS,
CLICKS TONGUE ]

04:44.821 --> 04:47.259
YOU KNOW,
EVERYONE'S REALLY FEELING

04:47.259 --> 04:48.995
THIS FAMILY-TOGETHERNESS
THING THAT I CREATED.

04:48.995 --> 04:50.531
IT REALLY MEANS A LOT
TO YOU, DOESN'T IT?

04:50.531 --> 04:51.566
YEAH.

04:51.566 --> 04:52.869
I MEAN, I NEVER
HAD THIS GROWING UP.

04:52.869 --> 04:54.239
ACTUALLY,
ONE CHRISTMAS,

04:54.239 --> 04:55.708
WE ONLY HAD A PICTURE
OF A CHRISTMAS TREE.

04:55.708 --> 04:58.546
IT WAS, LIKE, THIS BIG.
IT WAS REALLY, REALLY SMALL.

04:58.546 --> 04:59.782
WOW.

04:59.782 --> 05:01.451
YEAH.

05:01.451 --> 05:04.457
MOM, YOUR GINGERBREAD HOUSE
IS AMAZING.

05:04.457 --> 05:05.793
WOW. PRETTY SWEET.

05:05.793 --> 05:07.262
IT'S A FRANK LLOYD WRIGHT,

05:07.262 --> 05:09.967
GLUTEN-FREE,
AND STRUCTURALLY SOUND.

05:09.967 --> 05:11.637
WOW. OH, HEY -- YOU KNOW,
THE ONLY THING

05:11.637 --> 05:13.941
MISSING FROM
THIS MASTERFUL CREATION

05:13.941 --> 05:15.945
IS A GINGERBREAD
DOGHOUSE.

05:15.945 --> 05:17.815
YES.
HINT. HINT.

05:17.815 --> 05:18.817
HINT. HINT.

05:18.817 --> 05:20.821
WELL, IF YOU
DO GET A DOG,

05:20.821 --> 05:23.592
YOU'LL KNOW SANTA'S REAL,
'CAUSE I'D NEVER GET YOU ONE.

05:23.592 --> 05:24.794
HINT. HINT.

05:24.794 --> 05:26.330
JACKIE: [ CHUCKLES ]
CAN SOMEONE HELP ME LIGHT

05:26.330 --> 05:27.399
THE HANUKKAH MENORAH...

05:27.399 --> 05:29.870
AND THE KWANZAA KINARA
AND DIWALI DIYA?

05:29.870 --> 05:32.508
MY BELL SLEEVES
ARE A REAL FIRE HAZARD.

05:32.508 --> 05:33.910
UH, YEAH.

05:33.910 --> 05:36.549
YOU KNOW, I'M CELEBRATING
EVERY HOLIDAY THIS SEASON

05:36.549 --> 05:39.254
SO BERT'S LESS CONFUSED.

05:39.254 --> 05:41.725
THIS WEEK IS
ABOUT JESUS' BIRTHDAY,

05:41.725 --> 05:44.396
EIGHT DAYS OF OIL,
THE ATTAINMENT OF NIRVANA,

05:44.396 --> 05:46.467
AND BLACK PEOPLE
BEING AWESOME.

05:46.467 --> 05:49.305
AND DON'T FORGET THAT
I'M FASTING FOR RAMADAN, TOO.

05:49.305 --> 05:51.810
YOU DO KNOW THAT FASTING
MEANS NOT EATING, RIGHT?

05:51.810 --> 05:52.812
IT'S THE HOLIDAYS.

05:52.812 --> 05:53.981
I MEAN, I THINK
WE CAN AFFORD

05:53.981 --> 05:55.517
TO TREAT OURSELVES
A LITTLE.

05:55.517 --> 05:57.954
IT ALL STARTS TO GET FUZZY
AFTER WE PUT THE KIDS TO BED.

05:57.954 --> 05:59.925
YES, I REMEMBER
TELLING THEM

05:59.925 --> 06:01.327
NOT TO COME OUT
OF THEIR ROOMS TILL MORNING

06:01.327 --> 06:03.832
OR SANTA WOULDN'T BRING THEM
ANYTHING OVER $40.

06:03.832 --> 06:06.571
AND THEN I REMEMBER
DIANE FALLING.

06:06.571 --> 06:08.073
NO, I DIDN'T FALL.
I NEVER FALL.
MM-HMM.

06:08.073 --> 06:09.876
I REMEMBER
WHEN I LEARNED TO WALK.

06:09.876 --> 06:11.045
IT WAS INSTANT.

06:11.045 --> 06:14.351
WELL,
THE KIDS ARE ASLEEP,

06:14.351 --> 06:15.887
SO I GUESS
I'D BETTER BE GOING.

06:15.887 --> 06:17.056
[ THUD ]
OHH!

06:17.056 --> 06:18.793
OH! OH! DIANE.

06:18.793 --> 06:19.929
ARE YOU OKAY?
ARE YOU OKAY?

06:19.929 --> 06:21.698
OH, NO. I'M OKAY.
I'M OKAY.

06:21.698 --> 06:23.335
ARE YOU OKAY?
OH!

06:23.335 --> 06:25.371
[ LAUGHING ] DIANE, Y-YOU'RE --
YOU'RE SMASHED.
WHAT?

06:25.371 --> 06:27.809
NO, I'M --
YOU'RE LIKE, "AAH!" BAM!

06:27.809 --> 06:28.978
[ CHUCKLES ]

06:28.978 --> 06:30.882
YOU MUST GIVE ME
THE RECIPE FOR THAT GLURG.

06:30.882 --> 06:32.318
GLOGG.
GLURG.

06:32.318 --> 06:33.687
GLOGG.
GLURG.

06:33.687 --> 06:35.357
IT'S LIKE "GLO," GLOGG.
GLURG.

06:35.357 --> 06:38.095
GLORG, DIANE. GLORG.

06:38.095 --> 06:40.499
SO, IT WAS
KATE'S STUPID GLOGG

06:40.499 --> 06:42.837
THAT MADE US LIKE THIS.

06:42.837 --> 06:44.006
WHAT WAS IN THAT WINE?

06:44.006 --> 06:46.042
IT WAS MOSTLY RAISINS.

06:46.042 --> 06:48.347
YES, BUT WHAT WAS
IN THOSE RAISINS, KATE?

06:48.347 --> 06:51.353
[ GROANS ]

06:51.353 --> 06:52.455
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

06:52.455 --> 06:55.961
I'M PROVING
I DIDN'T DO THIS.

06:55.961 --> 06:57.797
LOOK.

06:57.797 --> 06:59.534
THIS IS ALL
THAT WE DRANK, OKAY?

06:59.534 --> 07:02.072
WITH SOME CLOVES
AND ORANGE PEEL.

07:02.072 --> 07:04.410
THAT'S IT.
AND THIS BOTTLE
OF ABSINTHE.

07:04.410 --> 07:08.651
WHOA. WE DANCED
WITH THE GREEN FAIRY.

07:08.651 --> 07:09.886
THIS HAS YOUR NAME
WRITTEN ALL OVER IT.

07:09.886 --> 07:10.988
NO, IT DOESN'T, DIANE.

07:10.988 --> 07:11.957
AH.

07:11.957 --> 07:13.927
OH, IT DOES.

07:14.728 --> 07:16.532
YEAH, BUT I DON'T EVEN
KNOW HOW IT GOT HERE.

07:16.532 --> 07:19.370
WELL, THEN HOW DID IT
GET IN THE PUNCH?

07:19.370 --> 07:21.908
AND WHY ARE YOU
IN HALF A SANTA SUIT?

07:21.908 --> 07:23.411
AND MOST IMPORTANTLY...

07:23.411 --> 07:28.019
[ BREATHES SHAKILY ]
...IS THIS WHO I AM NOW?

07:28.019 --> 07:31.025
GUYS, THE DOG JUST CHEWED
A HOLE THROUGH BERT'S DESK!

07:31.025 --> 07:32.961
WELL, YOU SAID
YOU WANTED A DOG.

07:32.961 --> 07:34.130
NOT THAT KIND!

07:34.130 --> 07:36.001
NOW, IF YOU COULD DIRECT US
TO THE PRESENTS,

07:36.001 --> 07:38.005
WE'D LIKE TO OPEN THEM,
IF THAT'S NOT TOO MUCH TROUBLE.

07:38.005 --> 07:39.908
YEAH,
I LOVE PRESENTS.

07:39.908 --> 07:42.914
SURE.

07:42.914 --> 07:44.083
WHERE ARE THEY?

07:44.083 --> 07:45.084
THEY'RE GONE!

07:45.084 --> 07:46.754
YOU MEAN...

07:46.754 --> 07:48.590
[ GASPS ]

07:48.590 --> 07:50.928
ALL: N-O-O-O-O-O-O!!

07:54.836 --> 07:56.038
[ SIGHS ]
DID YOU FIND THEM YET?

07:56.038 --> 07:57.574
NO, BUT IT'S ONLY
BEEN 30 SECONDS.

07:57.574 --> 07:58.642
HOW ABOUT NOW?

07:58.642 --> 08:01.080
COOL YOUR SHORTS,
MY YOUNG CONSUMER.

08:01.080 --> 08:06.723
HELLO? PRESENTS?
WHERE ARE YOU?

08:06.723 --> 08:08.660
YOU KNOW WHAT?
IT'S FINE, YOU GUYS.

08:08.660 --> 08:09.863
WE'LL JUST GO ON INSTAGRAM
AND LOOK AT PICTURES OF
OUR FRIENDS' PRESENTS.

08:09.863 --> 08:12.701
[ BOTH SIGH ]
YEAH.
LET'S GO, BERT.

08:12.701 --> 08:16.007
HOW ABOUT YOU GUYS?
YOU FIND ANYTHING?

08:16.007 --> 08:18.011
I LOOKED EVERYWHERE.
NO, YOU DIDN'T.

08:18.011 --> 08:19.547
YOU PUT ON
KATE'S PERFUME

08:19.547 --> 08:20.816
AND DANCED IN FRONT
OF THE MIRROR.

08:20.816 --> 08:22.385
I LOOKED EVERYWHERE.

08:22.385 --> 08:24.891
LET'S NOT FIGHT. REMEMBER,
THIS IS ALL HER FAULT.

08:24.891 --> 08:26.760
WHAT? NO.

08:26.760 --> 08:29.064
I JUST WANTED US ALL
TO BE TOGETHER ON CHRISTMAS.

08:29.064 --> 08:31.402
AND WHAT'S
WITH THIS CONFETTI?

08:31.402 --> 08:33.038
OH, THIS IS SNOW!

08:33.038 --> 08:35.409
YEAH, I THINK
YOU WERE SAYING YOU NEEDED IT

08:35.409 --> 08:36.778
FOR OUR WINTER WONDERLAND
OR SOMETHING.

08:36.778 --> 08:38.715
WHAT?

08:40.151 --> 08:41.654
OKAY,
"WINTER WONDERLAND"?

08:41.654 --> 08:43.157
I WOULD NEVER SAY THAT.
THAT'S SO LAME.

08:43.157 --> 08:44.560
I'M PRETTY SURE
YOU DID.

08:44.560 --> 08:46.196
WHY WOULD YOU
SHRED ALL THIS?
I DIDN'T.

08:46.196 --> 08:47.565
I DIDN'T EVEN KNOW
WE HAD A SHREDDER.

08:47.565 --> 08:48.733
BEEN LIVING HERE
A YEAR,

08:48.733 --> 08:50.036
YOU DIDN'T REALIZE
WE HAD A SHREDDER?

08:50.036 --> 08:51.873
AND I SAY, AGAIN,
WHAT DOES SHE DO ALL DAY?

08:51.873 --> 08:53.844
PFFT!

08:55.713 --> 08:59.587
[ GASPS ]
IT'S A WINTER WONDERLAND!

08:59.587 --> 09:02.058
SEE? TOLD YA
YOU SAID IT. FACE.

09:02.058 --> 09:04.730
THIS IS MY CASE
AGAINST THE BOTANICAL GARDEN.

09:04.730 --> 09:07.869
WHO DID THIS?
WHO DID THIS?!

09:07.869 --> 09:11.877
I'M DOING IT!
I AM SHREDDING MY FILES!

09:11.877 --> 09:13.045
GOOD FOR YOU, BABY.

09:13.045 --> 09:15.048
I'M DONE
WITH THE CONSUMERISM.

09:15.048 --> 09:17.486
IF I STOP MAKING MONEY,
WE'RE FREE.

09:17.486 --> 09:19.824
YOU KNOW, BYE--
BYE-BYE, CORRUPT CASE.

09:19.824 --> 09:22.562
TOODLE-OO,
SOULLESS JOB.

09:22.562 --> 09:23.731
HEY, YOU'VE BEEN
SINGING THAT SONG

09:23.731 --> 09:24.733
SINCE BEFORE
WE WERE MARRIED, SISTER.

09:24.733 --> 09:25.735
YOU KNOW WHAT?
WHAT?

09:25.735 --> 09:26.837
I'M GONNA CALL DOUG...
MM-HMM?

09:26.837 --> 09:29.008
...RIGHT NOW,
AND I AM GONNA TELL HIM

09:29.008 --> 09:32.481
THAT HE DOES NOT HAVE ME
TO DENY CLIMATE CHANGE ANYMORE.

09:32.481 --> 09:34.484
YEAH.
[ RINGING ]

09:34.484 --> 09:36.221
VOICEMAIL.

09:37.590 --> 09:40.595
UH, DOUG, IT'S PETE.

09:40.595 --> 09:42.766
IT WOULD BEHOOVE YOU
TO CALL ME BACK.

09:42.766 --> 09:44.235
IT'S 1:47
IN THE MORNING.

09:44.235 --> 09:46.606
I'LL BE UP
FOR THE NEXT 48 HOURS.

09:46.606 --> 09:47.976
[ LAUGHS ]

09:47.976 --> 09:50.514
[ LAUGHING ] OH.
THAT WAS INTOXICATING!

09:50.514 --> 09:51.916
THAT WAS
INTOXICATING!

09:51.916 --> 09:53.786
YOU WANT A REAL HIGH?
YEAH.

09:53.786 --> 09:54.788
CALL HIM BACK.

09:54.788 --> 09:58.896
[ CHUCKLING ]
OH, YEAH. OH, YEAH.

09:58.896 --> 10:02.869
HEY, DOUG! IT'S PETE!
IT'S 1:48!

10:02.869 --> 10:05.007
WHY DIDN'T YOU CALL ME BACK?!
[ LAUGHS ]

10:05.007 --> 10:06.042
DDO IT AGAIN.

10:06.042 --> 10:07.812
THAT'S A GOOD IDEA.
[ RINGING ]

10:09.214 --> 10:10.216
DOUG!!

10:10.216 --> 10:12.887
OH, MY GOD.
WHAT?

10:12.887 --> 10:17.763
I CALLED HIM 16 TIMES
BETWEEN 1:47 AND 3:38.

10:17.763 --> 10:19.600
WELL, DID YOU REACH HIM?
DID YOU QUIT?

10:19.600 --> 10:20.969
[ CHUCKLES ]
I-I DON'T KNOW.

10:20.969 --> 10:23.641
WELL, I TRIED TO STOP HIM,
BUT DOES HE LISTEN?

10:23.641 --> 10:25.110
[ SCOFFS ]
STORY OF MY LIFE.

10:25.110 --> 10:26.278
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

10:26.278 --> 10:28.583
IF IT'S DOUG,
I'M NOT HERE.

10:28.583 --> 10:30.787
HI!

10:30.787 --> 10:32.524
HI!
HI!
HI!

10:32.524 --> 10:35.796
SO, I THINK
YOU HAVE MY MARYS.

10:35.796 --> 10:37.800
WHAT? I DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

10:37.800 --> 10:38.702
AHA.

10:38.702 --> 10:40.672
AH!

10:40.672 --> 10:42.676
[ CHUCKLING ]
THEY'RE HAVING A TEA PARTY.

10:42.676 --> 10:44.746
THAT'S FRIGGING ADORABLE.

10:44.746 --> 10:46.182
THAT ONE. SHE DID IT.
WHAT?!

10:46.182 --> 10:47.851
OH, DON'T LOOK
SO SURPRISED.

10:47.851 --> 10:49.955
I CAN'T HELP IT. SOMETHING
HAPPENED TO MY EYEBROWS.

10:49.955 --> 10:52.026
HANG ON -- CAN WE JUST GO BACK
TO WHAT SHE DID WRONG?

10:52.026 --> 10:54.564
♪ JINGLE BELLS, JINGLE BELLS ♪

10:54.564 --> 10:57.269
♪ THERE ARE LOTS OF BELLS ♪

10:57.269 --> 10:59.273
♪ THEY'RE -- ♪
OOH. UH, WHOOPS.

10:59.273 --> 11:00.942
UH, UH...OKAY.

11:00.942 --> 11:02.946
♪ JINGLE BELLS ♪

11:02.946 --> 11:04.282
OOPS. SORRY.

11:04.282 --> 11:06.018
OOH, SHH! SORRY!

11:06.018 --> 11:07.722
WHAT ARE YOU DOING!?

11:07.722 --> 11:08.757
SHH!

11:08.757 --> 11:11.028
YOU'RE GONNA WAKE
THE BABY JESUSES!

11:11.028 --> 11:13.566
NO! DON'T SHUSH ME!
THIS IS MY HOUSE!

11:13.566 --> 11:15.870
I'M SHUSH--
SHUSHING FOR JESUS!

11:15.870 --> 11:18.742
[ SIGHS ]
OHH, UGH.

11:18.742 --> 11:20.211
[ CHUCKLING ] OH.

11:20.211 --> 11:22.749
THAT'S WHY I TOOK THEM,
'CAUSE IT'S THE THREE OF US.

11:22.749 --> 11:24.152
IT'S KATE, ME, AND...

11:24.152 --> 11:26.656
THE ONE WITH
THE DEAD EYES IS DIANE.

11:26.656 --> 11:27.925
EXCEPT WE'RE
DEFINITELY NOT VIRGINS.

11:27.925 --> 11:29.294
[ CHUCKLES ] HA!

11:29.294 --> 11:32.801
I AM NOT EVEN GONNA ASK
WHY THE MOTHERS OF OUR LORD

11:32.801 --> 11:35.639
WERE EATING
JALAPEÑO POPPERS.

11:35.639 --> 11:36.808
[ GASPS ]

11:36.808 --> 11:39.646
JALAPEÑO POPPERS!
BAR FOOD. MEG WAS HERE.

11:39.646 --> 11:40.948
GET THE LUSH
ON THE PHONE.

11:40.948 --> 11:43.621
OKAY.

11:43.621 --> 11:44.756
[ RINGING ]
MEG: HELLO?

11:44.756 --> 11:46.259
MEG, DO YOU KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED LAST NIGHT?

11:46.259 --> 11:49.197
ARE YOU THE ONE WHO SPIKED
THE PUNCH WITH ABSINTHE?

11:49.197 --> 11:51.201
THAT IS A CRIMINAL OFFENSE
AND WOULD BE YOUR THIRD STRIKE.

11:51.201 --> 11:53.705
THAT'S WHY YOU GUYS
WERE ACTING SO WEIRD.

11:53.705 --> 11:55.576
I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU DRANK
THE ABSINTHE WITHOUT ME.

11:55.576 --> 11:56.945
I DROPPED IT OFF
FOR KATE LAST WEEK

11:56.945 --> 11:58.648
SO WE COULD DRINK IT
TOGETHER ON CHRISTMAS,

11:58.648 --> 11:59.650
BUT I DIDN'T OPEN IT.

11:59.650 --> 12:01.654
ABSINTHE?
YEAH, BUT --

12:01.654 --> 12:03.290
OKAY, WE GIVE ALCOHOL
TO EACH OTHER FOR CHRISTMAS

12:03.290 --> 12:05.627
AND BIRTHDAYS
AND BANK HOLIDAYS AND...

12:05.627 --> 12:06.696
DON'T FORGET THURSDAYS.

12:06.696 --> 12:08.065
WOW,
WE DRINK TOO MUCH.

12:08.065 --> 12:10.203
BUT THAT'S NOT
THE POINT RIGHT NOW.

12:10.203 --> 12:12.707
YEAH, THE POINT IS
I GOT ATTACKED BY A COYOTE.

12:12.707 --> 12:15.579
WHAT?!
ARE YOU OKAY?

12:15.579 --> 12:17.048
NO! I'M IN THE E.R.
ON CHRISTMAS!

12:17.048 --> 12:19.787
IT'S ALL...
DRUNK SANTAS AND HOBOS.

12:19.787 --> 12:21.256
HOW DID YOU
GET ATTACKED BY A COYOTE?

12:21.256 --> 12:23.994
WELL, YOU SAID TO COME OVER
FOR THE BEST PARTY EVER.

12:23.994 --> 12:25.664
[ ACE OF BASE'S
"THE SIGN" PLAYING ]
HELLO?

12:25.664 --> 12:27.701
♪ IS ENOUGH, ENOUGH? ♪

12:27.701 --> 12:31.675
♪ I SAW THE SIGN,
AND IT OPENED UP MY EYES ♪

12:31.675 --> 12:33.178
♪ I SAW THE SI-- ♪

12:33.178 --> 12:37.720
♪ LIFE IS DEMANDING
WITHOUT UNDERSTANDING ♪

12:37.720 --> 12:39.256
♪ I SAW THE SIGN,
AND IT OPENED UP MY EYES ♪

12:39.256 --> 12:40.958
OH, MY GOD.

12:40.958 --> 12:42.829
♪ I SAW THE SIGN ♪

12:42.829 --> 12:44.365
♪ NO ONE'S GONNA
DRAG YOU UP ♪

12:44.365 --> 12:47.771
♪ OR PUT YOU IN THE LIGHT
WHERE YOU BELONG ♪

12:47.771 --> 12:50.342
♪ BUT WHERE DO YOU BELONG? ♪

12:50.342 --> 12:52.079
NOT HERE.

12:52.079 --> 12:53.248
WAY TO BRING IT DOWN.

12:53.248 --> 12:55.318
WELL, WE WERE HAVING
SO MUCH FUN.

12:55.318 --> 12:57.656
I'M SORRY.
WE SANG TOGETHER?

12:57.656 --> 12:59.826
OKAY, BUT WHAT DOES THAT
HAVE TO DO WITH THE COYOTE?

12:59.826 --> 13:03.099
AND I ASK AGAIN,
WE SANG TOGETHER?!
YEAH.

13:03.099 --> 13:04.769
AND THEN DIANE WENT OUTSIDE
TO GO LOOK FOR CHESTNUTS.

13:04.769 --> 13:06.071
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT A CHESTNUT IS,

13:06.071 --> 13:07.741
BUT I'M PRETTY SURE
THEY DON'T GROW ON DRIVEWAYS.

13:07.741 --> 13:09.077
I DID?

13:09.077 --> 13:11.682
I HAVEN'T DONE THAT
SINCE I WAS A GIRL.

13:11.682 --> 13:12.817
OH, WE USED TO
ROAST THEM

13:12.817 --> 13:14.720
IN FRONT OF THE FIRE
WITH PAPA.

13:14.720 --> 13:17.191
CHESTNUTS.

13:17.191 --> 13:19.964
CHESTNUTS.

13:19.964 --> 13:24.271
OH, I'LL PICK YOU
THE FINEST CHESTNUTS, PAPA.

13:24.271 --> 13:27.944
AND, OH, HOW THEY'LL JUMP
AND THEY DANCE ON THE FIRE.

13:30.148 --> 13:35.291
WELL, HELLO THERE,
LITTLE THING.

13:35.291 --> 13:36.326
[ SNARLS ]

13:36.326 --> 13:40.668
OH, MY.
AREN'T YOU FRIENDLY?

13:40.668 --> 13:43.239
AREN'T YOU FRIENDLY?

13:43.239 --> 13:47.346
I FOUND US A DOG
FOR THE KIDS.

13:47.346 --> 13:50.719
OH, WAIT,
THE DOG IS A COYOTE?

13:50.719 --> 13:52.256
MY DOG IS A COYOTE?

13:52.256 --> 13:54.259
I THINK THAT DOG IS A WOLF.
MEG: YEAH, IT COULD HAVE
BEEN A WOLF.

13:54.259 --> 13:56.296
OKAY, WELL, WHATEVER IT IS,
I THINK WE CAN ALL AGREE

13:56.296 --> 13:57.899
THAT IT'S A WILD ANIMAL.

13:57.899 --> 14:02.341
COME ON. COME ON, FELLA.
OUTSIDE. GO.

14:02.341 --> 14:04.378
WAIT, WHY ARE YOU
GETTING RID OF OUR DOG?

14:04.378 --> 14:06.348
THAT DOG WAS A COYOTE.

14:06.348 --> 14:09.087
IT WAS A WOLF.
THAT WAS OUR ONLY PRESENT.

14:09.087 --> 14:11.725
OKAY, WELL, GUYS, CHRISTMAS
ISN'T ONLY ABOUT PRESENTS.

14:11.725 --> 14:14.863
[ ALL GROAN ]
HOW CAN YOU PEOPLE EVEN BE
TALKING ABOUT PRESENTS

14:14.863 --> 14:17.836
WHEN THERE'S A SEEMINGLY
DEAD WOMAN IN YOUR BATHTUB?

14:20.841 --> 14:23.345
[ GASPS ]
MRS. STEINBERG?

14:23.345 --> 14:25.716
PETE: WHAT'S WARREN'S
TEACHER DOING HERE?

14:25.716 --> 14:27.420
PATTY!

14:27.420 --> 14:29.223
[ GASPS ]
I'LL WORK THE BAKE SALE!

14:29.223 --> 14:30.726
[ ALL SIGH ]
I KNEW SHE WASN'T DEAD.

14:30.726 --> 14:32.229
ME, TOO.
[ CHUCKLES ]

14:32.229 --> 14:33.398
I KNEW SHE WASN'T DEAD,
EITHER,

14:33.398 --> 14:34.967
BUT I REALLY
WANTED ATTENTION.

14:38.440 --> 14:40.377
YOU SURE I CAN'T GET YOU
A ROBE OR SOMETHING?

14:40.377 --> 14:42.347
OH, NO, NO.
I'M COMFORTABLE LIKE THIS.

14:42.347 --> 14:44.251
SO,
WHY ARE YOU HERE?

14:44.251 --> 14:47.356
OH, I FELL ASLEEP
IN YOUR TUB

14:47.356 --> 14:49.393
AFTER YOU FED ME
THAT DEVIL JUICE.

14:49.393 --> 14:51.264
YEAH, BUT WHAT HAPPENED
TO YOUR CLOTHES?

14:51.264 --> 14:53.000
OH, PETER TOOK THEM.

14:53.000 --> 14:54.069
[ GASPS ]

14:54.069 --> 14:55.338
WHAT?

14:55.338 --> 14:57.040
WELL, I WAS CAROLING

14:57.040 --> 14:59.278
WITH MY ALL-WOMEN'S
CHURCH GROUP.

14:59.278 --> 15:05.289
♪ FA LA LA LA LA,
LA LA LA LA ♪

15:05.289 --> 15:07.260
WHOO! WHOO! GOOD.

15:07.260 --> 15:10.365
MRS. STEINBERG? COME IN.
HAVE A DRINK WITH US.

15:10.365 --> 15:13.237
I-I THINK
SHE MEANT JUST ME.

15:13.237 --> 15:15.909
I'LL MEET YOU
AT THE CHUNS' PRAYER CIRCLE.

15:15.909 --> 15:17.746
[ CHUCKLING ]
KATE! LOOK AT THIS!

15:17.746 --> 15:19.081
OH, MY GOD! PETE!
THAT'S A GREAT IDEA!

15:19.081 --> 15:20.350
I KNOW. I KNOW.

15:20.350 --> 15:22.020
IT'S THE CASE
I'VE BEEN WORKING ON.

15:22.020 --> 15:25.026
OH, WE CAN MAKE A WINTER
WONDERLAND FOR THE KIDS!
OH!

15:25.026 --> 15:27.363
YOU KNOW WHAT YOU NEED?
WHAT?

15:27.363 --> 15:28.499
AN ELF!

15:28.499 --> 15:32.272
WAIT...
THIS WAS MY IDEA?!

15:34.042 --> 15:36.446
DO I LOOK LIKE
AN ELF YET?

15:36.446 --> 15:38.984
ALMOST. THEY'RE JU--
THEY'RE JUST A LITTLE UNEVEN.

15:38.984 --> 15:40.788
MAKE YOURS
A LITTLE SHORTER.
OKAY.

15:40.788 --> 15:44.127
OH. NO,
YOU MADE IT TOO SHORT.

15:44.127 --> 15:45.863
NOW I HAVE TO MAKE
MINE SHORTER, TOO.

15:45.863 --> 15:47.032
OKAY, MAKE SURE
YOU GET IT RIGHT

15:47.032 --> 15:48.335
BECAUSE THE EYEBROWS
ARE THE CURTAINS

15:48.335 --> 15:49.904
TO THE WINDOWS
OF THE SOUL.

15:49.904 --> 15:52.910
OKAY.

15:52.910 --> 15:55.081
[ GASPS ]

15:55.081 --> 15:56.917
THEY'RE GORGEOUS!

15:56.917 --> 15:58.152
YOW!

15:58.152 --> 16:00.290
WE JUST CREATED
THE PERFECT CHRISTMAS MOMENT!

16:00.290 --> 16:02.059
LET'S --
LET'S TAKE A PICTURE.

16:02.059 --> 16:03.061
NO.
YES!

16:03.061 --> 16:04.397
COME ON, DIANE,
BE FUN.

16:04.397 --> 16:05.399
DIANE.
OKAY, OKAY, OKAY.

16:05.399 --> 16:06.901
OKAY, HERE.

16:06.901 --> 16:09.374
I GOT IT. I GOT IT.
OH, HANG ON.

16:09.374 --> 16:12.412
MEG, CAN YOU WATCH
MY LITTLE PUPPY, PLEASE?

16:12.412 --> 16:14.316
COME ON. OKAY.

16:14.316 --> 16:16.887
YOU KNOW, HE LOOKS
A LITTLE LIKE A COYOTE.

16:16.887 --> 16:19.091
HE LOOKS
A LOT LIKE A COYOTE.

16:19.091 --> 16:21.361
HERE WE GO. HERE WE GO.
SQUISH IN.
OKAY. OW.

16:21.361 --> 16:22.898
[ SIGHS ]
OKAY.

16:22.898 --> 16:24.067
SEE? I THINK THE THREE OF US
COULD BE GREAT FRIENDS.

16:24.067 --> 16:25.536
I REALLY DO.
[ CHUCKLES ]

16:25.536 --> 16:28.074
[ CAMERA BEEPING ]

16:28.074 --> 16:29.310
WHY ISN'T IT GOING?

16:29.310 --> 16:31.314
WHY ISN'T IT GOING?

16:31.314 --> 16:33.216
IT'S -- IT'S -- IT'S COMING.
IT'S COMING.

16:33.216 --> 16:34.352
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

16:34.352 --> 16:36.222
[ FLAMES WHOOSH ]
CHEESE!
CHEESE!

16:36.222 --> 16:37.258
[ ALL SCREAMING ]

16:37.258 --> 16:39.261
IT'S ON FIRE!
FIRE!

16:39.261 --> 16:41.398
OH, MY GOD!
THAT DOG BIT ME!

16:41.398 --> 16:42.934
GET IT OUT!
GET IT OUT!

16:42.934 --> 16:44.271
FIRE! FIRE!

16:44.271 --> 16:45.372
WE'RE SO UNPREPARED
FOR THIS!

16:45.372 --> 16:47.911
HO, HO --

16:47.911 --> 16:49.246
FIRE!!

16:49.246 --> 16:51.416
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

16:51.416 --> 16:53.253
KATE,
OPEN THE DOOR!

16:53.253 --> 16:56.426
OKAY! OKAY!
OPEN THE DOOR! OPEN THE DOOR!

16:56.426 --> 16:58.262
GET IT OUT!
OPEN THE DOOR!

16:58.262 --> 17:01.302
OPEN IT! OPEN IT!
AAH!

17:01.302 --> 17:03.940
SUIT IS MELTING!
HANDS ARE HOT!

17:03.940 --> 17:05.944
[ GRUNTS ]

17:08.214 --> 17:11.220
I STILL DON'T UNDERSTAND
HOW I GOT INTO YOUR SANTA SUIT.

17:11.220 --> 17:13.391
WE WERE TALKING ABOUT

17:13.391 --> 17:14.626
HOW YOU WERE SICK
OF MAKING SO MUCH MONEY.

17:14.626 --> 17:16.362
WHAT?

17:16.362 --> 17:19.201
♪ YOUR HOSPITALITY ♪

17:19.201 --> 17:20.370
OH.

17:20.370 --> 17:23.208
SO, UM, WHY DO YOU
WANT TO QUIT YOUR JOB?

17:23.208 --> 17:27.048
BECAUSE CRASS MATERIALISM
IS THE WORST PART OF CHRISTMAS.

17:27.048 --> 17:29.153
YOU WANT TO KNOW
THE WORST PART OF CHRISTMAS?

17:29.153 --> 17:31.590
CRASS MATERIALISM.
I JUST SAID THAT.

17:31.590 --> 17:34.295
NO, IT'S WHEN THE KIDS
STOP BELIEVING IN SANTA.

17:34.295 --> 17:36.366
YEAR AFTER YEAR,
I SEE THE KIDS STOP BELIEVING

17:36.366 --> 17:39.070
IN THE MAGIC
OF CHRISTMAS.

17:39.070 --> 17:41.875
CHILDHOOD IS OVER,
AND FRESH-FACED INNOCENCE

17:41.875 --> 17:44.046
IS REPLACED
BY MORE PORNOGRAPHY

17:44.046 --> 17:46.584
THAN YOU CAN
SHAKE A STICK AT.

17:46.584 --> 17:49.256
SOMEDAY, BERT'S NOT GONNA
BELIEVE IN SANTA ANYMORE.

17:49.256 --> 17:50.424
THAT'S THE TRUTH.

17:50.424 --> 17:52.863
MRS. STEINBERG,
I'M GONNA HAVE TO ASK YOU

17:52.863 --> 17:54.299
TO TAKE OFF
YOUR CLOTHES.

18:00.477 --> 18:02.346
SHOW TIME.

18:06.421 --> 18:09.125
HO! HO! HO!

18:09.125 --> 18:11.330
SANTA?

18:11.330 --> 18:15.403
IS THAT REALLY YOU?!

18:15.403 --> 18:16.940
BYE-BYE!
BYE. BYE, GUYS!

18:16.940 --> 18:18.443
KIDS:
BYE, MRS. STEINBERG!

18:18.443 --> 18:20.112
BYE, DIANE!
L'CHAIM TO US ALL!

18:20.112 --> 18:22.416
BYE-BYE! THANK YOU!

18:22.416 --> 18:24.220
[ SIGHS ]

18:24.220 --> 18:26.190
SO, WHAT'S THE DEAL
WITH THE PRESENTS?
YEAH?

18:26.190 --> 18:27.359
I MEAN, IT FEELS LIKE
WE'RE BEING PUNISHED

18:27.359 --> 18:28.895
FOR SOMETHING
WE DIDN'T DO.

18:28.895 --> 18:31.232
COME ON, GUYS. CHRISTMAS
ISN'T JUST ABOUT PRESENTS.

18:31.232 --> 18:32.268
IT'S ABOUT MEMORIES.

18:32.268 --> 18:34.205
BUT YOU CAN'T
REMEMBER ANYTHING.

18:34.205 --> 18:35.240
ABOUT YESTERDAY,
BUT TODAY,

18:35.240 --> 18:36.643
WE HAD A LOT
OF GREAT MEMORIES.

18:36.643 --> 18:38.479
WE MADE SNOW,
WE GOT TO HANG OUT

18:38.479 --> 18:40.650
WITH A VERY
COYOTE-LIKE WOLF.

18:40.650 --> 18:42.587
[ LAUGHTER ]
AND I SAW SANTA!

18:42.587 --> 18:44.290
YEAH,
AND BERT SAW SANTA.

18:44.290 --> 18:47.195
SO,
I JUST WANT TO SAY...

18:47.195 --> 18:50.401
THANK YOU, KATE,
FOR BRINGING US ALL TOGETHER.

18:50.401 --> 18:53.340
PETE:
YOU KNOW, AS I SIT HERE,

18:53.340 --> 18:55.477
I CAN'T HELP
BUT THINK THAT...

18:55.477 --> 18:58.182
WE HAVE SO MUCH
TO CLEAN UP.

18:58.182 --> 19:00.687
[ CHUCKLES ]
I THINK IT'S NICE.

19:01.655 --> 19:03.926
IT FINALLY FEELS
LIKE CHRISTMAS.

19:03.926 --> 19:05.596
HEY,
WHAT'S THAT SMELL?

19:05.596 --> 19:07.065
[ SNIFFS ] WARREN.

19:07.065 --> 19:08.702
[ SIGHS ]
SMELLS MORE LIKE HILLARY.

19:08.702 --> 19:10.638
WHAT?!
IT SMELLS
LIKE BURNT PLASTIC.

19:13.142 --> 19:16.148
WHAT IS GOING ON?
WHAT IS THAT SMELL?

19:16.148 --> 19:18.620
BERT: OH, A BIKE!

19:18.620 --> 19:20.422
SANTA WAS HERE!
I KNEW IT!

19:20.422 --> 19:23.428
YES, HE WAS, SON.
YES, HE WAS.

19:23.428 --> 19:27.435
♪ WE WISH YOU
A MERRY CHRISTMAS ♪

19:27.435 --> 19:29.406
♪ WE WISH YOU
A MERRY CHRISTMAS ♪

19:29.406 --> 19:32.244
♪ WE WISH YOU
A MERRY CHRISTMAS ♪

19:32.244 --> 19:36.184
♪ AND IT'S SO HIGH UP HERE ♪

19:36.184 --> 19:38.422
WELL, WE FOUND
THE PRESENTS.

19:38.422 --> 19:41.027
I MEAN, THE BIKE
LOOKS PRETTY SALVAGEABLE.

19:41.027 --> 19:43.297
SANTA BROUGHT ME A BIKE
BECAUSE I WAS A GOOD BOY.

19:43.297 --> 19:45.168
I WORKED HARD IN SCHOOL,
I SHOWERED EVERY DAY,

19:45.168 --> 19:47.071
AND I HELPED KATE
WITH HER PARTY JUICE.

19:47.071 --> 19:48.408
WAIT, WHAT?!
COME AGAIN?

19:48.408 --> 19:50.411
WHAT?
I SHOWERED EVERY DAY.

19:50.411 --> 19:52.281
WELL,
ALMOST EVERY DAY.

19:52.281 --> 19:53.350
NO, NO, NO.
THE OTHER PART.

20:07.241 --> 20:09.245
♪ IT WASN'T ME ♪

20:09.245 --> 20:10.414
♪ IT WASN'T ME ♪

20:10.414 --> 20:11.316
YOU HEAR THAT, LADIES?
I DIDN'T DO IT!

20:11.316 --> 20:13.319
CONGRATULATIONS,
KATE.

20:13.319 --> 20:16.459
AND, OH, THANK YOU SO MUCH
FOR BEING SO HELPFUL BERT.

20:16.459 --> 20:18.629
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]
YES, THANK YOU, BERT.

20:18.629 --> 20:20.165
OH, GOD.

20:20.165 --> 20:21.167
WHAT?
IT'S DOUG.

20:21.167 --> 20:24.272
DOUG!
HEY, LISTEN, I --

20:24.272 --> 20:26.143
YES.

20:26.143 --> 20:29.248
I WOULD LOVE TO COME TO
WORK ON CHRISTMAS DAY.

20:29.248 --> 20:30.317
YEAH.

20:30.317 --> 20:32.020
I DIDN'T QUIT.

20:32.020 --> 20:34.258
HE DIDN'T QUIT!
I DIDN'T QUIT MY JOB!

20:34.258 --> 20:35.393
HE DIDN'T QUIT!
IT'S A CHRISTMAS MIRACLE!

20:35.393 --> 20:36.996
YAY! HALLELUJAH!

20:36.996 --> 20:38.332
WELL, I'M GONNA GO
LOOK FOR THE COYOTE.

20:38.332 --> 20:40.068
YOU SHOULD COME.
UH, IT'S A WOLF.
BE CAREFUL.

20:43.541 --> 20:46.213
♪ I SAW THE SIGN,
AND IT OPENED UP MY EYES ♪

20:46.213 --> 20:49.418
♪ AND I AM HAPPY NOW
